<div xmlns:perseus="http://www.perseus.org/meta/perseus.rdfs#" xmlns:dctype="http://purl.org/dc/dcmitype/" xmlns:tufts="http://www.tufts.edu/" xmlns:alph="http://alpheios.net/namespaces/tei" class="alpheios-lex-text_container en">
    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n2499" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δοῦπος</span></b>  (cf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κτύπος</span>): any dull, heavy sound, as the
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">thunder</span> at the gates of a besieged town, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀμφὶ πύλᾱς ὅμαδος καὶ δοῦπος ὀρώρει</span> |
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πύργων βαλλομένων</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 9.573</span></i>; of the <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">din</span> of
          battle, compared to the echo of woodmen's axes, <i><span class="en">Il. 16.635</span></i>; the <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">roar</span> of
          the sea, <i><span class="en">Od. 5.401</span></i>; or of a mountain
          torrent, <i><span class="en">Il. 4.455</span></i>. Cf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δουπέω</span>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
